textAfterTable: 14 Songs Album Review Not a group in the normal sense, the Texas Northside Kings are instead a group of hot young Austin-based guitarists and singers (Eve Mensees, Johnny Moeller, Mike Keller, Shawn Pittman, Seth Walker, Nick Curran) doing their thing in front of a veteran crackerjack band made up of drummer Willie Sampson, bassist Jeffery Plummer, organist and pianist Earl Gilliam, and sax legend Spot Barnett, and the result is a fun sampler of down-and-dirty contemporary electric Texas blues.
